This article is a press gaggle by Press Secretary Josh Earnest en route to Elkhart, Indiana. Earnest discusses President Obama's upcoming speech in Elkhart, focusing on the argument the President is making about strengthening the economy and advocating for the middle class. He also addresses questions about the presidential campaign, frustrations with the current debate, the progress made in the economy, the Zika virus, the situation in the Mediterranean, the President's commencement speeches, and the opioid crisis. Earnest mentions that there is no official White House position on the gorilla incident at the Cincinnati Zoo.